what are some good cameras for photography i'm getting a new yorkshire terrier and my brother is going to get a golden retriever i want to get a good camera to photograh them what are some good cameras with tripods thanks love yorkielover i would stick with a canon nikon or fuji point and shoot model they are robust enough to give you good shots simple enough to not bog you down with options but still have a good set of manual modes to allow you to grow i have had good success with amvona tripods they are inexpensive but decent quality i've had one of their travel tripods at for about years now and it workds great when looking at a tripod make sure the head has a quick release plate and bubble levels nothing worse than trying to get a quick shot but you can't get the camera off the tripod or setting up for a ladscape or portrait shot only to know that the tripod was not level and all your images come out with a tilt to them Digital photography Photography Leica Tripod (photography) Nikon Corporation Binoculars Canon T90 Nikon D70 Konica Minolta Rangefinder camera Camcorder Street photography Mouse (computing) Stereoscopy War of the Worlds (2005 film) Photographic film Panoramic photography Bluetooth Canon EF lens mount Nikon FM2 Single-lens reflex camera Secure Digital card Medium format Photographic lens Amateur astronomy Macro photography Contax Floppy disk Raw image format Stop motion Movie projector Closed-circuit television Bubble Bobble Cinematography Game controller Professional video camera Digital cinema Sundial Digital cinematography Traditional animation Depth of field Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Steadicam Advanced Photo System Nikon FE Super Mario 64 Diablo II: Lord of Destruction Katamari Damacy Nikon FM Revolver EXpanded MultiPlayer Canon PowerShot G Disposable camera Digital camera Doom 3 Visual Basic Nikon FE2 Manual transmission GunBound Inkjet printer BZFlag GoldenEye 007 Volleyball Nintendo Oscilloscope Filmmaking Vehicles in Unreal Tourn